data.name: 2025 Annual Iowa Turkey Shoot
data.note: Iowa teams can register for any day and shoot on any day during the competition window, 11/1-11/30.  Scoring information and Practiscore file will be sent out to teams after registration closes and before 10/31.  Medals will be awarded as follows:  Squad awards for 1st-3rd Rookie, Intermediate, Senior, and Non-Collegiate Open.  Individual awards for 1st-3rd Rookie, Intermediate entry level, Intermediate advanced, Senior Junior Varsity, and Senior Varsity.  Individual HOA for both male and female.  We will also give 1st, 2nd, and 3rd place medals for “best costume”.  Coaches can submit photos of any athlete who elects to compete in either a Halloween or Thanksgiving themed costume. Payments for entry fees should be sent to East Iowa Lead Heads VIA check or Venmo.

data.name: 2024 TX SASP Season Opener
data.note:
COACHES!  READ THIS! -  I'm trying something a little different to hopefully make registering squads with less than 4 athletes a little easier.  There are 5 slots open in each bay, however, ONLY 16 GUNS ARE ALLOWED TO SHOOT IN EACH BAY PER RELAY.  If you are entering a squad in a bay that already has another team occupying some of the slots, please count the number of guns in the other squads and do not enter more than 16 total guns in the bay.

Please no not tie up slots if you do not have committed athletes and squads to fill them.  If I see what are obviously "place holders", they will be removed.

data.name: Southeast Open Invitational
data.note: Hello fellow SASP athletes, teams and parents, You are cordially invited to the the Southeast Invitational, President’s Weekend February 16-18, 2024, hosted at 17 South Rod and Gun Club in beautiful Flemming, GA. We are just south of Savannah. Our invitational is open to any teams of any classifications and divisions. We will have all disciplines open for competition including revolver. Single entries will be allowed in each discipline in accordance with the SASP handbook. Individual awards will be High Score in each discipline per division. Team awards will be top three squads in each discipline per division. Youth will have an open division. Awards for Collegiate and Collegiate Open will be combined. There will be an awards banquet following the shooting Saturday morning. Lunch and the Banquet is included with registration. Coaches and range helpers eat free. Please consider encouraging your parents to help score. They can contact Marion to sign up. Registration is $25 per gun. There currently is no match hotel, but there are many hotels and one KOA campground within 2-3 miles of the range. Range address is: 5899 N Coastal Hwy, Fleming, GA 31309 All teams are invited so let everyone you can know! Please confirm your attendance before February 1 and the approximate number of shooters each day, even if you are not fully ready to squad up by then. Any questions contact Deb @ 17southsasp@gmail.com or Marion @ SASPCoachMarion@gmail.com
